Sarah Murnaghan, the 10-year-old Pennsylvania girl whose need for new lungs sparked a national debate on how donor organs are prioritized, is finally back at home after six months in the hospital.

A family spokeswoman has said Sarah was discharged today from The Children's Hospital of Philadelphia.

She later was carried into her family's Newtown Square home, where the entrance was festooned with balloons and bore a big sign saying 'Welcome Home, Sarah!'

