We've been tracking the 11-year-old girl's battle with cystic fibrosis since June, when her family began a public campaign to get their little girl a new set of lungs

Sarah received two sets of lungs this summer as she struggles with the effects of end-stage cystic fibrosis.

The operations came after a federal judge intervened in her parents' lawsuit challenging national transplant rules that put her at the end of the waiting list for adult lungs.

Hmother, Janet Murnaghan, wrote in a Facebook post late Monday that she and her daughter had 'cried tears of joy' and wrote: 'WE ARE GOING HOME TOMORROW'.

'We entered CHOP on Feb. 19, more than six months ago. I never could have imagined the journey that lay in front of us,' Murnaghan wrote in the post, thanking God, Sarah's donors and all those who supported the family.

She said she plans to speak with reporters today.

